data.description: Motivated sellers!  Seller has an FHA loan which is assumable.  Welcome home to 116 Bay Club Parkway located in beautiful North East Maryland.  This two story colonial has been well maintained and is ready for it's new owners.  As you enter the home you are greeted by the natural light of the open two story foyer.  To the right you will find the formal living room and to the left an office area currently setup as a bedroom.  Heading into the eat in kitchen you will find a center island with breakfast bar, granite countertops, tile backsplash, 42" cabinetry, pendant lighting as well as recessed lighting.  Off the kitchen you will find a living room featuring a floor to ceiling stone gas fireplace.  Also on the main level you will find a formal dining room as well as a half bath.  Heading upstairs you will find a large primary suite featuring a huge walk in closet, jetted soaking tub, stall shower with glass doors, 2 vanities, and a private water closet.  Additionally on the 2nd floor you will find the laundry area as well as 3 bedrooms and a shared bathroom.  Heading down to the finished lower level you will find another large recreation room perfect for setting up a game space or theater, a bonus room, and a full bathroom.  Heading out back you will find a large deck with a screened in gazebo off the main floor and just a few steps down you will find a nice sized paver patio featuring a grilling station as well as a fenced in rear yard with a storage shed.  This home is equipped with an owned solar system (NO lease or installment payments.  The power bill is currently $9.00/ month) and a 20kw whole house generator that runs on propane.  This home literally has it all and is located just a short drive outside the North East where you will find plenty of restaurants, boutiques, and shopping areas with easy access to I95 and route 40.  This home is only available due to a job relocation.  Make your appointment today, you will not be disappointed.
